I managed to make the process, so i will post here if someone needs/wants to to this.

1 - Did all the formating and etc.... at the ssd;
2 - Set to manual partitioning;
3 - choose "/" on the new SSD;
4 - Choose "/home" on my old home partition and unchecked the format box;
5 - Choose the same username of old instalation when asked;
6 - Install;
7 - Everything was the same way it where on the old HD when started for first time, only needed to redownload most apps.

Or AUR also have WPS-office in the repository , 
you can install it using : yaourt -S wps-office  

PS : if you need to search any package use : yaourt -sS {pacage-name}

